properties.areaDesc: Juneau Borough and Northern Admiralty Island
properties.headline: High Wind Warning issued January 9 at 10:36PM AKST until January 11 at 12:00AM AKST by NWS Juneau AK
properties.description:
* WHAT...Taku winds. Northeast winds 30 mph with gusts up to 80
mph expected.

* WHERE...Douglas, Downtown Juneau, West Juneau, and Thane.

* WHEN...From now until midnight AKST Friday night.

* TIMING...Gusty winds will continue to increase through the night
with frequent gusts to 60 mph. Peak gusts will occur Friday
morning and Friday afternoon when gusts will be around 80 mph
before easing Friday evening.

* IMPACTS...Objects will be blown around in the wind. Blowing
snow could cause low visibility at times. Power outages are
possible. Travel will be difficult, especially for high
profile vehicles.
properties.instruction:
People should avoid being outside in forested areas and around
trees and branches. If possible, remain in the lower levels of
your home during the windstorm, and avoid windows. Use caution if
you must drive.

NWSheadline: HIGH WIND WARNING REMAINS IN EFFECT UNTIL MIDNIGHT AKST FRIDAY NIGHT
